## Code Review Complete

I've completed the targeted code review of `middleware/wrap_writer.go` following the chi router code review protocol. The review is saved to `/sessions/quirky-practical-cerf/mnt/QPB/benchmarks/run_001/chi/haiku/code_reviews/CHI-30_review.md`.

### Summary of Findings

**3 bugs identified:**

1. **[CRITICAL BUG - Lines 202-204, 221]** Push method type mismatch
   - The `Push()` method (HTTP/2 server push) is defined on `*httpFancyWriter` but the var assertion expects it on `http2FancyWriter`
   - Will cause compile error

2. **[HIGH BUG - Line 209]** Double-counting of bytes in ReadFrom
   - When tee is enabled, `io.Copy()` calls `Write()` multiple times (each incrementing byte counter), then line 209 adds the byte count again
   - Causes callers of `BytesWritten()` to receive incorrect metrics

3. **[MEDIUM - Lines 9, 107]** Deprecated io/ioutil usage  
   - Should use `io.Discard` instead of `ioutil.Discard` (consistent with recent "Remove last uses of io/ioutil" commits)

All findings include exact line numbers, severity levels, evidence, and recommended fixes as required by the protocol.
